FBIS4-23405 "drafr108_d_94010" FBIS-AFR-94-108 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Angola UNITA Condemns Government Raids UNITA Condemns Government Raids MB0606075194 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in Portuguese 0600 GMT 6 Jun 94 MB0606075194 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro Portuguese BFN [Communique issued by the General Staff of the Armed Forces for the Liberation of Angola in Huambo on 5 June] [Text] The Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola aircraft are still bombing, with a truly murderous fury cities, towns and villages, all of them distent from war theaters. Over the past two days, 122 napalm, incendiary and fragmentation bombs were dropped in peaceful areas such as Huambo, Caala, Legua, Camenongue, Cangandala, Cangola, and Capenda Camulemba. The victims were all civilians: 103 people were killed and 341 others wounded on 4 and 5 June. The General Staff once more alerts the Angolan and international community to the serious consequences of the current escalation of violence for which only the government of Eduardo dos Santos is to blame. [Issued] Huambo, 5 June 1994. [Signed] Ben-Ben, chief of General Staff, and army general.
